**Ukraine war might just kickstart a nuclear energy renaissance**
The war in Ukraine may be the catalyst for a nuclear energy renaissance in the US, as the country seeks to reduce its dependence on Russian nuclear fuel imports. The Prohibiting Russian Uranium Imports Act, enacted in May 2024, bans imports of low-enriched uranium from Russia, but allows for waivers to import up to 1 million pounds per year through 2028. This law also unlocks $2.7 billion in federal funding to develop domestic production of nuclear fuel. The move is seen as a national security measure, as the US seeks to reduce its reliance on foreign supplies and promote domestic production. The law could also lead to the development of new nuclear power plants, which could provide a source of clean energy for the country.
